summary: The user calls Rens at ITC to sort out an issue with their order at the Honey Store in China Market. The user wants to know the status of their KGO chicken order which they placed with Manu. The call gets disconnected and they call again. The user wants to share photos via WhatsApp to help with the issue. The user wants to know when the package will be checked so they can pick it up. They are concerned that the package might be tampered with. The user informs Rens that they will send their ID via WhatsApp and the numbers they can be reached at are 96 and 99606.
speaker_a_summary: The user calls ITC to report an issue with their transfer to another king and to request a call back via WhatsApp in order to provide photos of the current situation to resolve the issue. The user states that their experience with the team has been requested and can be verified, and expresses suspicion that the packet might have been tampered with, and they believe the company will help them out by getting a replacement package. The user then provides their WhatsApp number to the representative.
speaker_b_summary: Mala honey store in China Market has the nickname Coco. Their phone number is 10 TIG. They can be reached via WhatsApp on the number 5061496006. Another number provided is 9606 but it is unclear if that is a double or not. The person on the other line said "eh bi rastî ecêb e ku xerîdarên min piştî ku hilberek xelet bikar tîne" which translates to "I can send you a photo of the person who stole my phone." They also said "ku hilberek xelet bikar tîne" translates to "who has my phone." The person is looking to locate their phone.
